    "title": "Enable reading of pchCommand before Complete()",
    "body": "I always found it useful to be able to see what message was incoming from another node as soon as the header had been received, but since #16202 it no longer appears to be possible to discern the pchCommand until the complete message has been received.\r\n\r\nIs there a way to determine the message as soon as the header has been received? This could be useful functionality in order to be able to reduce bandwidth, and for logging and debugging.",
